commentPostTextItems.html: an easy win for England, winning the toss gave them the big advantage, they skittled SL early on
England grab the full set of 2 points for the opening match. The world chumps Sri Lanka leave with zero
Match State: England won by 8 wkts
tune in for full coverage of tomorrow's matches: Kenya v Zim, and India v South Africa, 0945 GMT for both (English drizzle pending)
Stewart is apparently the Man of the match, a nice little comeback knock after endless analysis of his form in the past few weeks

commentTextItems.html: defends down the pitch, Jaya gathers it
guides it on the off side, but doesn't find the gap
flicks it away to mid wicket
a push into the covers raises a cheer for the 200
steps back and deflects it into the covers

commentPostTextItems.html: a mere 7 needed to kill this match off
